# Generating Sprites

Use the local `@tot/spritegen` CLI to produce consistent, transparent, game-ready
sprites. Do NOT hand-author sprites or invent image files. The visual identity is
defined in `creative/art-direction.md`; the default Style Pack is `brainrot`
(`tools/spritegen/src/styles/brainrot/`).

Character PORTRAITS are never generated — the canonical renders already exist in
`apps/client/src/assets/chars/` (wired via `apps/client/src/ui/portraits.ts`).
Generation is for IN-WORLD art: combat actors, environment props, ground plates,
FX, and UI frames.

## Always delegate to a background subagent

Generation blocks for ~1-3 minutes (and costs OpenAI credits). NEVER run it on the
main thread. Instead launch a background subagent and keep working:

- Use the Task tool with `subagent_type: shell` and `run_in_background: true`.
- Give it the exact command below, and tell it to report back the parsed `--json`
  result: `ok`, `chosen.verdict.score`, `outputs`, and reject paths.
- When it completes you'll be notified; then do the wiring on the main thread.

## Command

```bash
# World entity / prop (256x256):
pnpm --filter @tot/spritegen gen generate \
  --preset entity --subject "<concrete visual description>" \
  --id <snake_case_id> --n 3 --json

# UI frame (512, emits CSS 9-slice metadata):
pnpm --filter @tot/spritegen gen generate \
  --preset ui-frame --subject "<concrete visual description>" \
  --id <snake_case_id> --n 2 --json
```

- `--style brainrot` is the default; pass `--style` only to use another pack.
- `--subject` is a concrete art description, not the display name. For enemy-side
  characters, say "Corrupted" in the subject so the corruption treatment
  (sickly purple-grey, red eyes, glitch aura) is applied.
- Use `--n 3` (best-of-N) and parse `--json`. Add `--vision-qa` for a stricter check.

## Acting on the result

If `ok: true`, the chosen candidate beat QA (`chosen.verdict.score`). If `ok: false`,
inspect `error`/`rejects` and retry with a refined `--subject`. Outputs land in
`AvailableAssets/<Category>/` with a 1024 master in `tools/spritegen/out/masters/`.
Categories: `Areas/`, `Chars/`, `Cursors/`, `Entities/`, `FX/`, `Items/`, `UI/`.

## Wiring into THIS game (LottoTD Survivors)

Do NOT pass `--wire` — the auto-wiring targets (`apps/client/src/assets/manifest.ts`,
`packages/shared/...`) are inherited from Tales of Tileria and do not exist here.
Instead, wire by hand:

1. Copy/verify the output PNG under `AvailableAssets/` (generation puts it there).
2. Copy the game-size PNG into `apps/client/src/assets/` (e.g. `field/` for combat
   actors and props) and import it where it is consumed (combat actor texture maps
   in `apps/client/src/game/`, or CSS for UI frames).
3. Content definitions in `packages/content` stay presentation-free — texture
   lookups are keyed by id on the client side only.

Then bump the PATCH in `apps/client/src/version.ts` (registering art is a client change).

## Setup

Requires `tools/spritegen/.env` with `OPENAI_API_KEY` (gitignored). See `tools/spritegen/README.md`.
